  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNICEF Response to Mount Nyiaragongo volcano eruption in North Kivu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) and Health assistance to vulnerable communities affected by the volcano eruption. This UNICEF project provides safe water to volcano eruption-affected households, and interrupt cholera transmission within affected households and direct neighbors through the Case Area Targeted Interventions (CATI) approach. The project provides life-saving assistance to 83,630 people, including 15,054 women, 12,545 men, 56,031 children, and 8,363 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
